  "prompt": "In what year was Indian currency released with Mahatma Gandhi's photo on it?",
  "response": "Mahatma Gandhi\u2019s portrait was officially introduced on the standard Indian currency notes with the launch of the **Mahatma Gandhi Series** in **1996**. This series replaced the earlier set of banknotes that featured various motifs and symbols. Since 1996, all denominations of the Indian Rupee (\u20b9) have prominently displayed Gandhi\u2019s image on the obverse (front) side, symbolizing his pivotal role in India's independence movement and his enduring legacy.\n\n**Key Points:**\n- **Year Introduced:** 1996\n- **Series Name:** Mahatma Gandhi Series\n- **Significance:** First standard series to feature Gandhi\u2019s portrait on all denominations\n\nPrior to 1996, Gandhi appeared on some commemorative issues and specific denominations, but 1996 marked the beginning of his consistent presence across all standard Indian banknotes.",
